<statement>
<p>A triangle has sides with lengths <m>\displaystyle{a}={7.00}</m>, <m>\displaystyle{b}={13.57}</m>, and <m>\displaystyle{c}={16.31}</m>. Calculate all of the angles of this triangle.</p>
<p>A=<input type="text" style="width:5.8ch" name="qn1000" id="qn1000" value="" autocomplete="off" aria-label="Question 1 Part 1 of 3" class="text"/> (across from side of length <m>\displaystyle{a}={7.00}</m>)</p>
<p>
  B=<input type="text" style="width:5.8ch" name="qn1001" id="qn1001" value="" autocomplete="off" aria-label="Question 1 Part 2 of 3" class="text"/> (across from side of length <m>\displaystyle{b}={13.57}</m>)</p>
<p>
  C=<input type="text" style="width:5.8ch" name="qn1002" id="qn1002" value="" autocomplete="off" aria-label="Question 1 Part 3 of 3" class="text"/> (across from side of length <m>\displaystyle{c}={16.31}</m>)</p>
<p>Round to two decimal places.</p>


</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>25.01</li><li>55.03</li><li>98.28</li></ul></p><p>Because we have all three sides, we can use the law of cosines for the first angle.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{7}^{{2}}={13.57}^{{2}}+{16.31}^{{2}}-{2}{\left({13.57}\right)}{\left({16.31}\right)}{\cos{{\left({A}\right)}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{49}={184.1449}+{266.0161}-{442.6534}{\cos{{\left({A}\right)}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{401.161}=-{442.6534}{\cos{{\left({A}\right)}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{0.90626435942884}={\cos{{\left({A}\right)}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{A}={25.005886978304}={25.01}</m>.</p>
<p>For a second angle, we can use the shorter law of sines.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle\frac{{\sin{{\left({25.005886978304}\right)}}}}{{7.00}}=\frac{{\sin{{\left({B}\right)}}}}{{13.57}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{0.24525700909915}={\sin{{\left({B}\right)}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{B}={\arcsin{{\left(-{0.24525700909915}\right)}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{B}={55.03039467143}\approx{55.03}</m></p>
<p>The third angle we can calculate using the angle sum property.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{25.005886978304}+{55.03039467143}+{C}={180}^{\circ}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{C}={98.276900903284}\approx{98.28}</m></p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>